        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 3:03PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of training
thunderstorms along a line extending from Leasburg to near Roanoke
Rapids. Movement was north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph. Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Additionally, locally heavy rain is also
occurring with these storms and may lead to localized
flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Henderson, Oxford, Roxboro, Warrenton, Halifax,
Norlina, Littleton, Concord, and Weldon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
